(firstQuint)Gaze Contingent Feedback in Major Depressive Disorder (MDD).

 The study examines giving depressive participants gaze-contingent feedback as a novel attention training procedure.

 Half of the participants will receive contingent feedback while the other half would receive non-contingent "placebo" feedback.

